{
  "texts": [
    "Word embedding is a dense numerical representation of words that creates distributed representations where words with similar meanings or contexts are closer together in the vector space.",
    "This representation mechanism captures the semantic meaning of words.",
    "Several recent AES research studies employ word embeddings to capture context in the essay scoring process (Cozma et al. 2018; Dong and Zhang 2016; Dong et al. 2017; Tay et al. 2018; Liang et al. 2018; Hussein et al. 2020; Song et al. 2020a).",
    "C &W embeddings are trained using CNN with max-pooling.",
    "The objective of this embedding technique is to learn local context and task-specific representations by simultaneously training on multiple NLP tasks, including POS tagging and NER."
  ]
}